# Error Handling & Async (Mandatory)

Apply to every `.ts`/`.tsx` file. This is the #1 source of production incidents — get it right everywhere.

## Async discipline
- Any function that calls async code is `async` and **awaits** it. Never leave a floating promise.
- Use `Promise.all` (fail-fast) or `Promise.allSettled` (collect) deliberately — never fire-and-forget.
- Lint must pass `@typescript-eslint/no-floating-promises` and `no-misused-promises`.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD: floating promise + swallowed error
function place(input) { orderService.create(input).catch(() => {}); }

// ✅ GOOD: awaited; throws a typed error handled centrally
async function place(req, reply) {
  const dto = createOrderSchema.parse(req.body);
  const order = await orderService.create(dto);
  return reply.code(201).send(ok(order));
}
```

## Error handling
- **Never swallow errors.** Empty `catch {}` is forbidden. When you catch, you must recover, rethrow a typed error, or log-and-rethrow at the boundary.
- Throw **typed domain errors** (`NotFoundError`, `ValidationError`, `ConflictError`, `InsufficientStockError`, …), not bare `throw new Error('...')`.
- Map errors **once**, in the global handler (`setErrorHandler`) → standard envelope + correct status. Handlers throw; they don't format error responses.
- **Never leak internals** (stack, SQL, secrets) to clients. Log server-side with the request id; return a safe message + stable `error.code`.
- Wrap fallible ops where you can add value (translate/enrich/recover) — not blindly around everything.
- Clean up in `finally` or rely on transaction rollback so failures never leak connections/locks/reservations.

```typescript
// ✅ catch to enrich, then rethrow typed
try {
  return await repo.findByIdOrThrow(id);
} catch (cause) {
  if (cause instanceof NotFoundError) throw cause;
  throw new AppInternalError('Failed to load entity', { cause });
}
```
